[ Inaudible Speaker ]

00:29:42.230 --> 00:29:43.530
&gt;&gt; Janet Eilber: Can you hear?

00:29:43.530 --> 00:29:44.960
He's asking what the difference is

00:29:44.960 --> 00:29:48.180
between the Martha Graham
technique and ballet?

00:29:48.180 --> 00:29:49.900
You know you've got
two arms, two legs,

00:29:49.900 --> 00:29:55.130
how many different
things can you do?

00:29:55.130 --> 00:30:00.270
But Martha discovered as she was
searching for a style of movement

00:30:00.270 --> 00:30:07.010
that would reveal emotion she
discovered that emotion rides

00:30:07.010 --> 00:30:10.560 position:56%
on the breath when you laugh or when
you sob or when you are nervous,

00:30:10.560 --> 00:30:15.780
it changes your breath and she
developed a style of dancing driven

00:30:15.780 --> 00:30:20.010
by the torso, her contraction
being the exhale and the coiling

00:30:20.010 --> 00:30:25.370
in of the torso and the release
being the inhale and the sending

00:30:25.370 --> 00:30:29.100
out of energy and tonight
on stage all of the movement

00:30:29.100 --> 00:30:31.090
in the Martha Graham
works are driven

00:30:31.090 --> 00:30:36.420
by the torso, the core muscles.

00:30:36.420 --> 00:30:41.230
She used this energy to
also leverage herself

00:30:41.230 --> 00:30:44.160
against the floor and
to use gravity.

00:30:44.160 --> 00:30:45.900
She wanted to show effort.

00:30:45.900 --> 00:30:49.700
She wanted to show the human
condition as opposed to ballet

00:30:49.700 --> 00:30:55.550
which was very sort of antigravity
and above the ground she went

00:30:55.550 --> 00:31:00.940
into the ground and you will see
there's a series of wonderful falls

00:31:00.940 --> 00:31:04.790 position:56%
that she created that are part of
the Graham technique tonight in Cave

00:31:04.790 --> 00:31:10.150 position:56%
of the Heart you'll see Medea as her
heart is breaking just legs opening

00:31:10.150 --> 00:31:15.840
and the whole torso drops down
into the floor and then rebounds

00:31:15.840 --> 00:31:23.860
and recovers so it's a much more
shall I say gutsy percussive

00:31:23.860 --> 00:31:27.700
earthbound technique than ballet.

00:31:29.690 --> 00:31:31.510
&gt;&gt; Anne McLean: Anyone else?

